Admin Dashboard

The admin dashboard provides a central overview of the platform's key metrics, including the number of brands, total posts, vendors, customers/users, recent advert posting trends, income statement summary, upcoming expiring posts, vehicle count by types, post conditions, and a section for phone number correction requests.

Description:

This page offers administrators a snapshot of the platform's health and recent activity. At the top, it displays key statistics such as the total number of Brands, Total Post count with a trend indicator, the number of Vendors, and the number of Customers/Users. A graph shows the "Last 30 Days Advert Posting Report." An "Income Statement" provides a visual summary of income over the past months. The "Up Coming Expire Post" section lists posts nearing their expiration date. Pie charts display "Vehicle Count By Types" and "Post Condition" breakdowns. Finally, a section titled "What's up Phone Number Correction List [Private & Trade Seller Only]" lists users requesting phone number corrections. The left sidebar provides navigation to various admin sections.

Key Features:

  • Key Metric Overview: Displays counts for brands, posts, vendors, and users.
  • Recent Advert Trend: Visual representation of advert posting activity over the last 30 days.
  • Income Summary: Graphical overview of the platform's income statement.
  • Expiring Post Alerts: Lists posts that will expire soon.
  • Vehicle and Post Condition Breakdown: Pie charts showing the distribution of vehicle types and post conditions.
  • Phone Number Correction Requests: Section to manage user-submitted phone number corrections.
  • Comprehensive Navigation: Left sidebar for accessing all admin functionalities.

 

 

Admin - Post Advert > All Advert

This page displays a comprehensive list of all adverts posted on the platform, with details like ID, photo, short title, dealer, deadline, total view, status, position, and actions for management.

Description:

This page provides administrators with a full overview of all adverts. Each advert is listed with an ID, a thumbnail photo, a short title, the associated dealer's name or ID, the advert's deadline status, the total number of views, its current status, its position (likely for featured placements), and a set of action buttons for managing the advert (e.g., edit, delete). There are also filtering and search options at the top to help administrators find specific adverts based on various criteria. Bulk actions can be applied to selected adverts.

Key Features:

  • Comprehensive Advert Listing: Displays all adverts with key details.
  • Thumbnail Photos: Visual representation of each advert.
  • Detailed Information: Includes title, dealer, deadlines, views, status, and position.
  • Management Actions: Provides buttons for administrators to take action on individual adverts.
  • Filtering and Search: Options to narrow down the advert list.
  • Bulk Actions: Ability to apply actions to multiple selected adverts.

 

Admin - Post Advert > Add Car

This page provides a form for administrators to manually add new car adverts to the platform, including various vehicle details and listing options.

Description:

This page features a form for creating new car listings. It includes fields for vehicle specifics, pricing, images, and other relevant details needed for a car advert on the platform. Administrators can input all necessary information for a new car listing through this form.

Key Features:

  • Form to create new car adverts.
  • Fields for vehicle details, pricing, and images.
  • Comprehensive input options for car listings.

 

 

Admin - Post Advert > Add [Car/Motorbike/Part/Import Car]

This page provides a form for administrators to manually create new listings for the selected vehicle type or part, including relevant details and listing options.

Description:

This page features a form designed for creating new listings. It includes fields tailored to the specific vehicle type (car, motorbike, import car, import motorbike) or part, covering essential details, pricing, images, and other necessary advert information.

Key Features:

  • Form to create new listings.
  • Fields specific to the selected vehicle type or part.
  • Comprehensive input options for listings.

 

Admin - Post Advert > Listing Bill

This page displays a control panel for managing listing bills, showing created date, listing ID, service name, user name, package, price, payment status, paid date, and actions.

Description:

This page provides a table to manage listing bills. It shows when the bill was created, the associated listing ID, the name of the service billed, the username of the customer, the package purchased, the price, the payment status, the date of payment, and available actions for each bill.

Key Features:

  • Table listing all listing bills.
  • Displays key billing information.
  • Shows payment status and dates.
  • Provides actions for bill management.

 

Admin - Post Advert > Product Tags

This page allows administrators to manage product tags, showing the ID, name, slug, and actions for each tag. It includes options to create new tags and search existing ones.

Description:

This page displays a table of product tags used on the platform. For each tag, it shows a unique ID, the tag's name, its slug (URL-friendly version), and available actions for management (e.g., edit, delete). Administrators can use the "Create" button to add new tags and the search bar to find specific tags.

Key Features:

  • Table listing all product tags.
  • Displays ID, name, and slug for each tag.
  • Provides actions for tag management.
  • Option to create new product tags.
  • Search functionality for existing tags.

 

Admin - Users Menu

The "Users" menu provides administrators with tools to manage user accounts, including viewing all users, adding new users, managing roles and access control lists (ACLs), and viewing notifications.

Sub-menus:

  • All User:
    • Summary: Displays a list of all registered users with details like registration date, role, name, email, contact, total posts, and actions.
    • Key Features: User list, filtering and search, user details, management actions.
  • Add New User:
    • Summary: Provides a form for administrators to manually create new user accounts with role selection and personal details.
    • Key Features: User creation form, role assignment, personal information fields.
  • Role / ACL:
    • Summary: Allows administrators to manage user roles and their associated permissions (ACLs).
    • Key Features: Role listing, permission management, role creation/editing.
  • Notifications:
    • Summary: Displays a list of notifications sent to users, including details like user, vehicle type, brand, model, and actions.
    • Key Features: Notification list, filtering, notification details, deletion option.

 

Admin - User Log Menu

The "User Log" menu allows administrators to track user activity, including login history and a graphical overview of user access patterns.

Sub-menus:

  • All Logs:
    • Summary: Displays a detailed history of user logins, including user ID, username, login time, logout time, IP address, browser, device, and actions.
    • Key Features: Comprehensive login history, filtering and search options, user details, deletion of log entries.
  • Graph View:
    • Summary: Provides visual representations of user activity, including pie charts for browsers, user roles, devices, and a line chart for the log activity over time.
    • Key Features: Graphical overview of user access by browser, role, device, and activity timeline.

 

Admin - CMS Menu

The "CMS" (Content Management System) menu provides administrators with tools to manage the website's content, including pages, posts, categories, and SEO settings.

Sub-menus:

  • All Page:
    • Summary: Displays a list of all created pages with their title, creation date, status, and actions.
    • Key Features: Page listing, status overview, editing and deletion options.
  • New Page:
    • Summary: Provides a form to create new website pages with options for page title, content (WYSIWYG editor), and SEO settings.
    • Key Features: Page creation form, rich text editor, SEO title, keywords, and description fields.
  • All Post:
    • Summary: Displays a list of all blog posts with details like ID, thumbnail, title, category, post date, status, and actions.
    • Key Features: Blog post listing, category and status overview, editing and deletion options.
  • New Post:
    • Summary: Provides a form to create new blog posts with options for title, content (WYSIWYG editor), categories, and SEO settings.
    • Key Features: Blog post creation form, rich text editor, category selection, SEO title, keywords, and description fields.
  • Category:
    • Summary: Allows administrators to manage blog post categories, including adding new categories, editing existing ones, and viewing the category list.
    • Key Features: Category list, add new category form, edit and delete options.
  • Search Page Seo:
    • Summary: Lists items related to search page SEO, including ID, search item, and actions.
    • Key Features: Search page SEO item listing, editing options.

 

Admin - Blog Menu

The "Blog" menu provides administrators with tools to manage the platform's blog content, including viewing all blog posts, creating new posts, and managing blog categories.

Sub-menus:

  • Blog:
    • Summary: Displays a list of all blog posts with details like ID, thumbnail, title, category, post date, status, and actions.
    • Key Features: Blog post listing, category and status overview, editing and deletion options.
  • New Blog:
    • Summary: Provides a form to create new blog posts with options for title, content (WYSIWYG editor), categories, tags, featured image, and SEO settings.
    • Key Features: Blog post creation form, rich text editor, category and tag selection, featured image upload, SEO title, keywords, and description fields.
  • Category:
    • Summary: Allows administrators to manage blog post categories, including adding new categories with names, slugs, menu order, meta title, meta keywords, and meta description, as well as editing and deleting existing ones.
    • Key Features: Category list, add new category form with SEO options, edit and delete options.

 

Admin - Manage State

This page allows administrators to manage states within the platform, including adding new states, editing existing ones, and associating locations with them.

Description:

This page provides tools to manage geographical states. Administrators can add new states by providing a name and slug, and designate if it's a "Home" state. A list of existing states is displayed with their name, slug, type, country, post quantity, "Show in Home" status, and actions (edit). There's also a section to "Add New Location with State," allowing association of specific locations with a selected state.

Key Features:

  • Add new states with name and slug.
  • Mark states as "Home" states.
  • List existing states with key details.
  • Edit existing state information.
  • Add new locations linked to specific states.

 

Admin - Manage Engine Size

This page allows administrators to manage engine sizes available on the platform, including adding new sizes and assigning them to specific vehicle types.

Description:

This page provides tools to manage the engine sizes for vehicles. Administrators can add new engine sizes by specifying the size and associating it with a particular vehicle type (e.g., Car, Motorbike) using a dropdown menu. A list of existing engine sizes is displayed with their ID, vehicle type, engine size value, and actions (edit, delete).

Key Features:

  • Add new engine sizes.
  • Assign engine sizes to specific vehicle types.
  • List existing engine sizes with associated vehicle types.
  • Edit and delete engine size entries.

Admin - Help/FAQs

This page displays a list of user-submitted help requests or frequently asked questions, allowing administrators to view, update, and delete them.

Key Features:

  • Lists user-generated help requests/FAQs.
  • Displays the question, submitter details, status, and creation date.
  • Provides options to view, update/answer, and delete entries.
  • Search functionality to find specific queries.


 

Admin - Newsletter Subscribers

This page allows administrators to manage newsletter subscribers, including adding new subscribers and viewing a list of current subscribers with their name, email, subscription status, creation and modification dates, and actions.

Key Features:

  • Option to manually add new newsletter subscribers.
  • Displays a list of all subscribers with key details.
  • Shows subscription status (Subscribed/Unsubscribed).
  • Tracks creation and last modification dates.
  • Provides actions for managing subscribers (e.g., edit, delete).


Admin - Email Templates

This page lists all the email templates used by the platform, showing their subject, the associated blog/call back (if any), and actions to preview and edit them.

Key Features:

  • Comprehensive list of all email templates.
  • Displays the subject line of each template.
  • Indicates the related blog or call back function.
  • Provides actions to preview and edit the content of each template.
  • Search functionality to find specific templates.

 

Admin - Settings

This page allows administrators to configure various platform-wide settings, including time zone, company name, email configurations (CC, BCC, incoming, outgoing, bounce), currency, email footer signature, bank details, regular and featured ad prices, and requirement services text.

Key Features:

  • Configuration of time zone and company name.
  • Setup for CC and BCC email addresses.
  • Settings for incoming, outgoing, and bounce email accounts.
  • Currency selection.
  • Option to set a default email footer signature.
  • Fields to input bank details.
  • Control over regular and featured advert prices.
  • Text editor for requirement service information.
  • "Update Setting" button to save changes.

 

Admin - DB Backup & Restore

This page likely allows administrators to create backups of the platform's database and restore the database from previously created backups.

Key Features:

  • Option to initiate a database backup process.
  • List of available database backup files.
  • Functionality to download existing backup files.
  • Option to upload and restore the database from a backup file.
  • Information on backup size and creation date 

 

Admin - List of Modules

This page displays a list of all modules installed on the platform, showing their ID, name, type, added date, status, and available actions (view, edit, delete).

Key Features:

  • Comprehensive list of installed modules.
  • Displays module ID, name, and type.
  • Shows the date when the module was added.
  • Indicates the current status of each module (e.g., Locked, Enable).
  • Provides actions to view details, edit settings, and delete modules.
  • Search functionality to find specific modules.


Admin - ACLs (Access Control List)

This page allows administrators to manage access permissions for different modules and functionalities within the platform by defining permission titles and their corresponding keys.

Key Features:

  • Option to add new access control permissions by selecting a module, defining a permission title and a unique permission key.
  • Displays a list of existing access control permissions with their module, permission name, permission key, and actions (edit/delete).
  • Search functionality to find specific permissions.


Admin - My Account

This page allows the logged-in administrator to view and update their personal profile information.

Key Features:

  • Displays the administrator's first name, last name, contact numbers, address details, country, state/region, city, postcode, and contact email.
  • Provides fields to edit and update this personal information.
  • Includes an "Update" button to save any changes made to the profile.
  • Navigation tabs for "My Profile," "Trade Seller Page," "Video Gallery," "Change Password," and potentially other profile-related settings.

 

Admin - Photo Gallery Menu

The "Photo Gallery" menu allows administrators to manage images uploaded to the platform, organize them into albums, and configure gallery settings.

Sub-menus:

  • All Photo:
    • Summary: Displays a list of all uploaded photos with details like ID, thumbnail, title/caption, album, uploader, upload date, and actions (update, delete).
    • Key Features: Comprehensive photo listing, filtering by user and album, image details, update and delete options.
  • All Albums:
    • Summary: Lists all created photo albums with their ID, name, and actions (edit, delete).
    • Key Features: Album listing, album name display, edit and delete options for albums.
  • Gallery Settings:
    • Summary: Likely provides options to configure various settings related to the photo gallery display and functionality on the front-end.
    • Key Features: Settings for thumbnail sizes, display layouts, upload limits, etc.
